{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"71609aad-d395-4cb2-96bd-b6834c093ca3","content":"Two key changes when moving to xUnit v3 + MTP:\n\n**1. Filter syntax differs.** MTP doesn't use VSTest's `--filter`; it uses `--filter` with its own TFM-style expressions. The `FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests` (contains) becomes a wildcard, and `Trait` filtering uses brackets:\n\n```bash\n# Old (VSTest / xunit v2):\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n\n# New (MTP / xunit v3):\ndotnet test --filter \"/*IntegrationTests*[Category=Smoke]\"\n```\n\n**2. `Trait` attribute is gone in v3.** Replace it with `[Category]` (built-in to xunit.v3) or keep using `[Trait]` which still works but `[Category]` is the idiomatic replacement for category traits specifically.\n\nWould you like me to update your `IntegrationTests.cs` to use the v3 `[Category]` attribute?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"48f91051-2c83-400b-9162-891143fba52d","outputTokens":255,"requestId":"4C23:3CF0BE:D4DB56:10961C9:6A012A5D"},"id":"45ea2da4-d967-4075-9ba3-e94e4ac31132","timestamp":"2026-05-11T01:01:24.877Z","parentId":"8ad76088-d18c-49d8-819d-497801f67728"}
